-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party references and their licenses
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

parsers/gig_parser.py
  The GIG/DLS2 binary structure knowledge used in this file is derived from
  the reverse-engineering work documented in libgig:
    libgig — C++ cross-platform Gigasampler format file access library
    Copyright (C) 2003-2021  Christian Schoenebeck <cuse@users.sourceforge.net>
    https://www.linuxsampler.org/libgig/
    License: GNU General Public License v2.0 or later (GPL-2.0-or-later)
  The initial GIG format reverse engineering was carried out by
  Paul Kellett and Ruben van Royen; GigaStudio v3/v4 support was added
  by Andreas Persson. See libgig ChangeLog for full contributor list.
  This file is therefore also released under GPL-2.0-or-later.

parsers/sf2_parser.py
  Based on the publicly available SoundFont 2.04 File Specification,
  published by E-mu Systems / Creative Technology Ltd.
  The SF2 C++ classes in libgig were written by Grigor Iliev (GPL-2.0-or-later).
  This file is an independent reimplementation from the specification;
  no source code was copied. Released under GPL-2.0-or-later for consistency.

parsers/exs24_parser.py
  EXS24 binary format knowledge derived from:
    - exs2sfz (GPL-2.0): https://github.com/mqnc/exs2sfz
    - ConvertWithMoss (LGPLv3), Jürgen Moßgraber:
      https://github.com/git-moss/ConvertWithMoss
  This file is an independent reimplementation; no source code was copied.
  Released under GPL-2.0-or-later for consistency.

parsers/talsmpl_parser.py
  TAL-Sampler format knowledge partially informed by:
    - ConvertWithMoss (LGPLv3), Jürgen Moßgraber:
      https://github.com/git-moss/ConvertWithMoss
  XML structure verified against live .talsmpl files.
  This file is an independent reimplementation; no source code was copied.
  Released under GPL-2.0-or-later for consistency.

writers/krz_writer.py
  Kurzweil K2000 KRZ format knowledge partially derived from:
    - KurzFiler (GPL-2.0), Marc Halbrügge:
      https://kurzfiler.sourceforge.io/
  Binary field layout verified against community documentation and
  live .KRZ files. This file is an independent reimplementation;
  no source code was copied. Released under GPL-2.0-or-later.

parsers/sfz_parser.py
  Based on the publicly available SFZ v1/v2 community specification:
    https://sfzformat.com/
  No third-party source code used. Released under GPL-2.0-or-later
  for consistency with the rest of the project.

All other files (models/common.py, writers/e4b_writer.py,
writers/bank_splitter.py, writers/iso_builder.py,
processors/resampler.py, convert.py, test_pipeline.py)
  Original work. Released under GPL-2.0-or-later.

